---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="MIFIDPRU 8 Disclosure" description="MIFIDPRU 8 Disclosure — Hengistbury Investment Partners LLP.">

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/disclosures" class="back-link">← Disclosures</a>
      <p class="eyebrow">Regulatory Disclosure</p>
      <h1>MIFIDPRU 8 Disclosure</h1>
      <p class="meta">Hengistbury Investment Partners LLP &mdash; April 2026</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <article class="disclosure-body">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="doc-grid">
        <nav class="doc-toc">
          <ol>
            <li><a href="#introduction">Introduction</a></li>
            <li><a href="#own-funds">Own Funds</a></li>
            <li><a href="#own-funds-requirements">Own Funds Requirements</a></li>
            <li><a href="#remuneration">Remuneration Policy</a></li>
          </ol>
          <div class="toc-footer">
            <a href="/disclosures" class="back-link-sm">All disclosures</a>
          </div>
        </nav>

        <div class="doc-content">
          <section id="introduction">
            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>
              This disclosure is made by Hengistbury Investment Partners LLP (&ldquo;the Firm&rdquo;)
              in accordance with the Financial Conduct Authority&rsquo;s MIFIDPRU 8 rules, which
              require certain FCA-authorised investment firms to publish information on own
              funds, own funds requirements, and remuneration policies.
            </p>
            <p>
              The Firm is authorised and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority
              (FCA reference number available on the FCA Register). This disclosure is
              published annually and covers the period ending 31 December 2025.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="own-funds">
            <h2>2. Own Funds</h2>
            <p>
              The Firm&rsquo;s own funds are composed entirely of Common Equity Tier 1 (&ldquo;CET1&rdquo;)
              capital, principally comprising members&rsquo; capital and retained earnings. The Firm
              holds no Additional Tier 1 or Tier 2 instruments.
            </p>
            <p>
              The Firm maintains own funds in excess of the higher of its permanent minimum
              capital requirement, its fixed overheads requirement, and its K-factor requirement,
              as applicable under MIFIDPRU.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="own-funds-requirements">
            <h2>3. Own Funds Requirements</h2>
            <p>
              As a non-interconnected, non-systemically important investment firm (&ldquo;SNI firm&rdquo;)
              for MIFIDPRU purposes, the Firm&rsquo;s own funds requirement is determined as the
              higher of:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>The permanent minimum capital requirement of &pound;75,000;</li>
              <li>One quarter of the Firm&rsquo;s fixed annual overheads (the &ldquo;fixed overheads requirement&rdquo;); and</li>
              <li>Any applicable K-factor requirement.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              The Firm monitors its own funds position on an ongoing basis and maintains
              adequate capital resources to meet its regulatory requirements at all times.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="remuneration">
            <h2>4. Remuneration Policy</h2>
            <p>
              The Firm operates a remuneration policy that is consistent with and promotes
              sound and effective risk management. The policy is designed to avoid creating
              incentives that may lead to the taking of excessive risk.
            </p>
            <p>
              Remuneration at the Firm consists of fixed and variable components.
              Fixed remuneration reflects the relevant professional experience and
              organisational responsibility of each individual. Variable remuneration
              is discretionary and reflects performance over the relevant period,
              assessed against both financial and non-financial criteria.
            </p>
            <p>
              The Firm&rsquo;s remuneration arrangements are reviewed at least annually by the
              Firm&rsquo;s management to ensure they remain appropriate and consistent with the
              Firm&rsquo;s regulatory obligations and risk appetite.
            </p>
          </section>

          <div class="doc-footer">
            <p>Review date: April 2026</p>
            <p>
              Hengistbury Investment Partners LLP &bull; Partnership No: OC365747 &bull;
              Authorised and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero { background: var(--navy); padding: 3rem 0 4rem; }
  .back-link { display: inline-block; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; transition: color 0.2s; }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--gold); }
  .eyebrow { font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--gold); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .page-hero h1 { color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .meta { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .disclosure-body { padding: 4rem 0; background: var(--white); }
  .doc-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr; gap: 4rem; align-items: start; }
  .doc-toc { position: sticky; top: 90px; }
  .doc-toc ol { list-style: none; border-left: 2px solid var(--border); padding-left: 0; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .doc-toc a { display: block; padding: 0.45rem 0.75rem; font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--mid-gray); border-left: 2px solid transparent; margin-left: -2px; line-height: 1.4; transition: color 0.15s, border-color 0.15s; }
  .doc-toc a:hover { color: var(--navy); border-left-color: var(--gold); }
  .toc-footer { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding-top: 1rem; }
  .back-link-sm { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--mid-gray); }
  .back-link-sm:hover { color: var(--gold); }
  .doc-content section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .doc-content h2 { font-size: 1.4rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .doc-content p { color: #444; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .doc-content ul { color: #444; padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .doc-content li { margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .doc-footer { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding-top: 2rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .doc-footer p { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--mid-gray); line-height: 1.65; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .doc-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .doc-toc { position: static; } }
</style>
